<item>
            <title>[HBASE-9080] Retain assignment should be used when re-enabling table(s)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9080</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Region servers are picked in round robin fashion when a table is re-enabled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This results in poor data locality.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should use retain assignment when re-enabling table(s).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For initial discussion, see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6143&quot; title=&quot;Make region assignment smarter when regions are re-enabled.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6143&quot;&gt;HBASE-6143&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Since patches for 0.94 and trunk may turn out to be very different, this JIRA is for fixing the issue in 0.94 branch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks Lars, Elliot, Vladmir and Stack for providing opinions on this subject.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
